me.leoko.advancedgui.utils.components

Class ListComponent<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.leoko.advancedgui.utils.components.Component
      • me.leoko.advancedgui.utils.components.InteractionStateComponent<ListState<T>>
        • me.leoko.advancedgui.utils.components.ListComponent<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the items it contains
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.bukkit.event.Listener

    public class ListComponent<T>
extends InteractionStateComponent<ListState<T>>
    The ListComponent holds a list of items for each interaction and renders a list of components for the item list. It handles pagination.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ListComponent

        public ListComponent(String id,
                     Action clickAction,
                     Function<Interaction,List<T>> itemListGenerator,
                     ListItemBuilder<T> itemComponentBuilder,
                     int pageSize,
                     int stepSize)
        Instantiates a new ListComponent.
        Parameters:
        id - the id
        clickAction - the click action
        itemListGenerator - the item list generator: It should return a list of items for the given interaction. if all interactions should have the same list then use the other constructor.
        itemComponentBuilder - the item component builder: Given an interaction, item and the index it should return an component for this list item. The index is relative to the pagination. So it is between 0 and pageSize - 1.
        pageSize - the page size (i.e. how many components to show at once)
        stepSize - the step size (i.e. how many items to skip when going to the next page | usual values are 1 or pageSize)

        pageSize - the page size (i.e. how many components to show at once)
        stepSize - the step size (i.e. how many items to skip when going to the next page | usual values are 1 or pageSize)

      • refreshItems

        public void refreshItems(Interaction interaction)
        Reload items from the itemListGenerator or from the globalList and render the new components. The component is not reactive to list changes. So this method has to be called for any changes to the item list to be visible.
        Parameters:
        interaction - the interaction
